remarks.para:
Performs runtime validation and throws 
            for detectable misuse such as TermQuery on analyzed-only fields, Contains on keyword fields,
            and contradictory soft-delete conditions.

member.summary:
Registers a field to be excluded by default from Elasticsearch _source filtering.
Default excludes are applied only when no explicit excludes are set on the query;
setting any explicit exclude on a query will cause all default excludes to be skipped.

remarks.code:
query.FieldOr(g => g
    .FieldEquals(f => f.IsPrivate, false)
    .FieldEquals(f => f.CompanyId, companyIds)
);

member.summary:
Negated exact match. Generates BoolQuery { MustNot = TermQuery/TermsQuery }
on the non-analyzed (.keyword) field.
Null values are rewritten to .
